Parliament formally elected Gen. Emile Lahoud, the popular army commander who has the backing of powerful neighbor Syria, as Lebanon's next president.
Lahoud is to be sworn for a six-year term on Nov. 24, the day President Elias Hrawi leaves office.
Prime Minister Rafik Hariri has declined an informal invitation from Lebanon's new president to form the next government, sparking a political crisis in this country as it rebuilds from its devastating civil war.
Sources close to the prime minister, whose Cabinet has been in care-taker capacity since's swearing in of Lahoud as president, said Hariri turned down the invitation from Lahoud to select a new Cabinet.